title.rendered: Hobart vs Brisbane, Australia T20 League 2022: Today’s Match Preview, Fantasy Cricket Tips

content.rendered:
We have opted for a fantasy cricket team based on the recent performances, overall impact, and credit points.

Probable XIs

Hobart: Caleb Jewell, Ben McDermott, Zak Crawley, Tim David, Matthew Wade (c & wk), D’Arcy Short, Faheem Ashraf, Joel Paris, Nathan Ellis, Patrick Dooley, Riley Meredith

Brisbane: Usman Khawaja (c), Josh Brown, Marnus Labuschagne, Matt Renshaw, Sam Hain, Jimmy Peirson (wk), Michael Neser, James Bazley, Spencer Johnson, Mitchell Swepson, Matthew Kuhnemann

Pitch Report

Venue: Aurora Stadium, Launceston

(Based on the last 3 games)

1st innings average score: 154

2nd innings average score: 150

Wickets per innings: 8

Type: Balanced

Wins

Batting 1st: 67%

Batting 2nd: 33%

Fantasy Tips of the Day

Patrick Dooley has starred in the Ultimate Team in 9 of 10 games. In addition, his best figures (4 for 16) of the season came at the very venue.

At Launceston, Riley Meredith has bagged 12 wickets in only 7 outings.

Zak Crawley and Tim David have been scoring the bulk of the runs in the middle overs for Hobart. Between them, they have smashed 282 runs in the last 5 games.

In the previous contest between these teams, Matt Renshaw (41 off 31 and 1 for 12) and Michael Neser (3 for 27) were the captain and vice-captain of the Ultimate Team respectively.

In his last 5 games, Ben McDermott has collected a mere 22 runs.

In the last 3 matches at the venue, only one opener scored a fifty. The pacers, otherwise, ruled the roost. An average of 2 wickets fell in the powerplay.

1 / 5 ( 2 votes )
